CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1953, pg. 30 reads: "Banquet Highlight - ONe of the highlights of the second annual Terrace Village baseball banquet held at the Centre Avenue YMCA last Saturday night was the presentation of awards to various athletes and a "lucky team" baseball to honored guest Prothonotary David B. Roberts. Left to right are John Gant, who accepted the award for his brother, Roy, now in service; pitcher, Tom Chick, Roberts, William Berry, pitcher and president of Terrace Village, and Harold Tinker, who acted as master of ceremonies.  Tinker had carved the trophies presented to the players. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: John Gant, Tom Chick, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, William Berry, and Harold Tinker, standing in office of Centre Avenue YMCA for Terrace Village baseball banquet
